Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Implementation file: src/cli.ts (NEW FILE)
The last unit test passed (no-op). Now create the REQUIRED CLI entry point at src/cli.ts (the spec mandates it). It must:
- read all of stdin as text
- JSON.parse it into a scenario
- call runScenario from "./claim-office.js"
- write JSON.stringify(result) to stdout
- on any error (parse error or runScenario throw), write the error message to stderr and exit with a non-zero status code; no results written to stdout

Use Node's process.stdin/stdout/stderr. Minimal, idiomatic. Example:

import { runScenario } from "./claim-office.js";
let input = "";
process.stdin.setEncoding("utf8");
process.stdin.on("data", (chunk) => { input += chunk; });
process.stdin.on("end", () => {
  try {
    const scenario = JSON.parse(input);
    const output = runScenario(scenario);
    process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(output));
  } catch (error) {
    process.stderr.write(error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error));
    process.exitCode = 1;
  }
});

After creating it, verify it works end-to-end by piping the spec's schema example JSON into it via tsx, and confirm stdout is the expected results JSON and a bad input exits non-zero. Run `pnpm test` to confirm the 39 unit tests still pass (cli.ts has no tests but must not break the build).

